{"session_id":"svc-1778364211702640141","seq":0,"type":"session.start","ts":"2026-05-09T22:03:33.721298239Z","data":{"provider":"","model":"sonnet","sticky":{"key_present":true,"bonus":0},"utilization":{"observed_at":"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z"},"requested_harness":"claude","resolved_harness":"claude","harness_source":"request_harness","requested_model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","resolved_model":"sonnet","work_dir":"/var/tmp/ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-94a368b6-20260509T220324-9d0cc920","max_iterations":0,"prompt":"\u003cexecute-bead\u003e\n  \u003cinstructions\u003e\nYou are executing one bead inside an isolated DDx execution worktree. The bead\u0026#39;s \u0026lt;description\u0026gt; and \u0026lt;acceptance\u0026gt; are the completion contract — every AC must be provably satisfied by a specific code, test, or file you can point to after your commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Step 0: size check\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The bead is too big when any of these holds:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- More than ~6 ACs spanning unrelated subsystems.\u0026#xA;- AC mixes design, implementation, integration tests, and docs as separate top-level deliverables.\u0026#xA;- Description names multiple feature-sized sub-pieces.\u0026#xA;- More than ~500 lines across more than ~5 files in unrelated packages.\u0026#xA;- If the bead description exceeds 8000 bytes, treat Step 0 as a split-first pass and favor child-bead scoping before implementation.\u0026#xA;- Auto-decomposition is capped at depth 2: root beads may split once, decomposed children may split once more, and third-level splits must be rejected with an explanation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If too big, decompose — do not attempt the work:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;1. `ddx bead create` for each child slice (focused title, description, AC; copy parent\u0026#39;s labels and spec-id).\u0026#xA;2. `ddx bead dep add \u0026lt;child-id\u0026gt; \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt;` to record edges.\u0026#xA;3. `ddx bead update \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt; --notes \u0026#39;decomposed into \u0026lt;child-ids\u0026gt;\u0026#39;` so the decomposition is visible.\u0026#xA;4. Write `.ddx/executions/20260509T220324-9d0cc920/no_changes_rationale.txt` listing each child ID and slice, then stop.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;A clean decomposition is a successful attempt. Do not mix partial implementation with decomposition.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## How to work\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Read first. If the bead names files, specs, or prior beads, read them before editing — do not guess.\u0026#xA;- Cross-reference each AC against concrete evidence (test name, file path, function) before committing. If you cannot point at it, it is not done.\u0026#xA;- Run the project\u0026#39;s test and lint commands before committing. **Do not commit red code** — fix failures first.\u0026#xA;- Stage with `git add \u0026lt;specific-paths\u0026gt;`; never `git add -A` (the worktree may have unrelated WIP).\u0026#xA;- Commit exactly once when green; conventional-commit subject ending with `[\u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;]`. Stop after the commit.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s scope.\u0026#xA;- If you cannot finish, write `.ddx/executions/20260509T220324-9d0cc920/no_changes_rationale.txt` (what is done, what blocks, what a follow-up needs) before exiting. No commit and no rationale ⇒ DDx records `no_evidence_produced`. A well-justified no_changes beats a bad commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## no_changes contract\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;`.ddx/executions/20260509T220324-9d0cc920/no_changes_rationale.txt` must contain one:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- `verification_command: \u0026lt;cmd\u0026gt;` — repo cwd; exit 0 closes, nonzero rejects.\u0026#xA;- `status: open` + `reason: \u0026lt;retryable\u0026gt;` — open, smart retry.\u0026#xA;- `status: proposed` + `reason: \u0026lt;operator needed\u0026gt;` — operator lane.\u0026#xA;- `status: blocked` + `reason: \u0026lt;external blocker\u0026gt;` — blocked lane.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;No pseudo-statuses. Bare rationales and `status: needs_investigation` reject.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Reports\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Freestanding artifacts (investigation reports, findings docs) go under `.ddx/executions/20260509T220324-9d0cc920/` (the per-attempt evidence directory under `.ddx/executions/`). **Never write reports to `/tmp` or any path outside the repository** — out-of-repo paths are invisible to the post-merge reviewer and cause BLOCK on missing evidence. If the bead names a specific in-repo path, use it; else default to `.ddx/executions/20260509T220324-9d0cc920/\u0026lt;short-name\u0026gt;.md`. Stage and commit the report alongside code.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Mode and overrides\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;DDX_MODE=bead_execution: edit code/docs for bead AC. Only broad queue-steward default is overridden; tracker, merge-policy, verification, safety stay active. Bead description/AC override CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, and project defaults.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Review gate\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- The review is a gate, not an escape hatch — meet every AC in this pass.\u0026#xA;- Address every BLOCKING `\u0026lt;review-findings\u0026gt;` item; do not declare `no_changes` with blocking findings open.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Constraints\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Work only inside this execution worktree.\u0026#xA;- Keep `.ddx/executions/` intact — DDx uses it as execution evidence.\u0026#xA;- **Never run `ddx init`** — the workspace is initialized; running it corrupts the bead queue.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s named scope.\u0026#xA;- Do not rewrite CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, or other project-instructions files unless the bead asks.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## When the work is done\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;After the commit succeeds and every AC is verified, stop. Return control to the orchestrator — do not keep exploring or testing.\n  \u003c/instructions\u003e\n  \u003cbead id=\"ddx-94a368b6\"\u003e\n    \u003ctitle\u003ebead/conformance: add transition-matrix coverage to backend_conformance_test\u003c/title\u003e\n    \u003cdescription\u003e\nPROBLEM\u0026#xA;  cli/internal/bead/backend_conformance_test.go is the single shared test\u0026#xA;  suite that must pass against both the JSONL backend (backend_jsonl.go) and\u0026#xA;  the Axon backend (axon_backend.go). It covers create, update, claim, deps,\u0026#xA;  events, and close - but it does NOT exercise the TD-031 §3 transition\u0026#xA;  matrix. Two backends could silently diverge on transition side effects\u0026#xA;  (external_blocker_reason persistence on Blocked, claim-Extra cleanup on\u0026#xA;  Reopen, label management) without the conformance suite catching it.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;ROOT CAUSE\u0026#xA;  - cli/internal/bead/backend_conformance_test.go:53-166 enumerates test\u0026#xA;    cases for the existing surface but skips status-transition flows.\u0026#xA;  - cli/internal/bead/lifecycle.go:244-256 declares the legal transition\u0026#xA;    matrix; cli/internal/bead/lifecycle_conformance_test.go covers the\u0026#xA;    transition validator in isolation but does not run it through both\u0026#xA;    backends end-to-end.\u0026#xA;  - axon_backend.go and backend_jsonl.go each implement their own metadata\u0026#xA;    side effects; drift is undetected.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;PROPOSED FIX\u0026#xA;  - Extend cli/internal/bead/backend_conformance_test.go with a new test\u0026#xA;    block TransitionMatrix that, for each backend instance under test:\u0026#xA;      a. Walks every legal transition from lifecycle.go:244-256:\u0026#xA;         proposed -\u0026gt; {open, cancelled}\u0026#xA;         open -\u0026gt; {in_progress, blocked, proposed, cancelled}\u0026#xA;         in_progress -\u0026gt; {open, closed, blocked, proposed}\u0026#xA;         blocked -\u0026gt; {open, proposed, cancelled}\u0026#xA;         closed -\u0026gt; open (with ManualReopen)\u0026#xA;      b. For each transition, asserts:\u0026#xA;         - The persisted Status field changed.\u0026#xA;         - Required Extra side effects landed (external_blocker_reason on\u0026#xA;           Blocked, claim-Extra cleared on Reopen, etc.).\u0026#xA;         - Forbidden transitions return the expected validation error from\u0026#xA;           ValidateLifecycleTransition.\u0026#xA;  - Use existing test helpers in backend_conformance_test.go (the\u0026#xA;    parameterized factory pattern); do not introduce a new harness.\u0026#xA;  - Run the suite against both JSONL and Axon backends via the existing\u0026#xA;    parameterization at backend_conformance_test.go top.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;NON-SCOPE\u0026#xA;  - Changing the transition matrix or validator.\u0026#xA;  - Adding new transitions.\u0026#xA;  - Refactoring the conformance suite structure beyond appending the new\u0026#xA;    test block.\u0026#xA;  - Drift in event vocabulary (TD-031 §4); covered by separate event tests.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;INTERSECTIONS\u0026#xA;  - ddx-ca1c66ee (epic parent).\u0026#xA;  - No deps on B1/B2/B3; can run in parallel.\n    \u003c/description\u003e\n    \u003cacceptance\u003e\n1. cli/internal/bead/backend_conformance_test.go contains a new test (e.g. TestBackendConformance_TransitionMatrix) that walks every legal transition declared in lifecycle.go:244-256 and asserts both Status persistence and required Extra side effects against both backends.\u0026#xA;2. The new test asserts forbidden transitions (closed -\u0026gt; *, cancelled -\u0026gt; *, in_progress -\u0026gt; cancelled) return the expected ValidateLifecycleTransition error against both backends.\u0026#xA;3. The new test passes against both the JSONL backend and the Axon backend via the existing conformance parameterization.\u0026#xA;4. cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./internal/bead/... -run TestBackendConformance green.\u0026#xA;5. cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./internal/bead/... ./internal/agent/... ./cmd/... green.\u0026#xA;6. lefthook run pre-commit passes.\n    \u003c/acceptance\u003e\n    \u003clabels\u003ephase:6, area:bead, area:lifecycle, kind:test, spec:TD-031\u003c/labels\u003e\n    \u0